Use the standard library
This is how to rescale_to_unit of numbers:
   Remember that low is min of numbers
   Remember that high is max of numbers
   Remember that width is diff of high and low
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this numbers's length times:
      Remember that value is item i in numbers
      Remember that scaled is quotient of (diff of value and low) and width
      Add result to scaled
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is result
Now you know

>>> rescale_to_unit of [1.000000, 2.000000, 3.000000, 4.000000, 5.000000]
[0.000000, 0.250000, 0.500000, 0.750000, 1.000000]
>>> rescale_to_unit of [2.000000, 49.900000]
[0.000000, 1.000000]
>>> rescale_to_unit of [100.000000, 49.900000]
[1.000000, 0.000000]